<paragraph blockId="11.[227,1436,511,713]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Some specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Anseeuw, Puillandre, Utge &amp; Bouchet" authorityYear="2015" box="[470,715,511,537]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pleurotomariidae" genus="Perotrochus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pseudogranulosus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[470,715,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. pseudogranulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[726,819,512,538]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have over the years turned up in the shell trade as “ 
<emphasis box="[240,460,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName box="[240,306,547,573]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pleurotomariidae" genus="Perotrochus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cfr">P. cfr</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Metivier" authorityYear="1982" box="[320,460,547,573]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pleurotomariidae" genus="Perotrochus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="caledonicus">caledonicus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
”, supposedly originating from NW 
<collectingCountry box="[899,1007,546,572]" name="Australia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Australia</collectingCountry>
or even from the South 
<collectingCountry box="[1313,1383,546,572]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">China</collectingCountry>
Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Anseeuw P. &amp; Goto Y." box="[235,525,582,609]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref5148" refString="Anseeuw P. &amp; Goto Y. 1996. The Living Pleurotomariidae: 1. Elle Scientific Publications, Osaka." type="book" year="1996">Anseeuw &amp; Goto 1996</bibRefCitation>
). However, based on the lack of precise and trustworthy locality data, the lack of more recent confirmation of those alleged findings and, most of all, the general unavailability of such material for study, we reject these localities as intentionally or unintentionally unproven and unverifiable.
</paragraph>
